# *Direct variable type validators* (i.e., functions validating the types of
# strictly scalar variables _not_ indirectly referring to other variables).
#
# == See Also ==
#
# * zy:../*-declare/*-test/*-var.zy, providing indirect variable type
#   validators.

#FIXME: Shift all remaining scalar type validators here from the main codebase.
#Functions defined in the subsequent "*-alias_func" parcel require these
#validators.

# ....................{ TESTERS                            }....................
:func_ '[status=:bool] :int.is(:str value)' :func{
    # Dismantled, this is:
    #
    # * "(-|)", matching an optional prefixing negative sign.
    # * "<->", matching one or more digits. An obscure, but helpful, zsh-ism.
    [[ ${value} == ('-'|)<-> ]]
}:func <<'/---'
Report success only if the passed string is an *integer* (i.e., consists of only
an optional negative sign followed by one or more digits).
/---
